      "writtenOn": "2019-03-21T23:00:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is intentional. For booleans it doesn\u0027t really matter but in general I prefer to omit fields in generated *.proto, instead of setting them to their default values. This allows the server to substitute the default it wants.\n\nHere is is important for \u0027template\u0027 field. I want it to be None, so the generated proto has it empty, so LUCI Notify can substitute its own default. I try to avoid copying default values into lucicfg code.",
